@node "What_do" "What does the program do?"

                          @{fg highlight}Destination of program@{fg text}

  VBRControler is a simply program written in assembler which gives you a 
simply way of moving VBR table to Fast memory and back to Chip memory.

@endnode

@node "Description" "Description"

                               @{fg highlight}Description@{fg text}

  Program can be run from CLI/Shell or by clicking on its icon.
  Program have font-sensitive GUI and localization, so you just have to
push the right gadget.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

                                 @{fg highlight}Requirements@{fg text}

    To work program needs at least MC68010, Kickstar 2.0 (V37),
reqtools.library V2 (V38) and a bit of Fast memory.

@endnode

